				<h3 class="title">üñã Font Awesome</h3>
				<p>What is <a href="https://fontawesome.com/">Font Awesome</a> and why you need to know how to use it?</p>
				<p style="margin-top: 20px;">It is just an awesome tool for little icons if you want to make your life easier. You can place Font Awesome icons just about anywhere using a style prefix and the icon‚Äôs name. We‚Äôve tried to make it so that icons take on the characteristics and appear alongside text naturally.</p>
				<p style="margin-top: 20px;">To reference an icon, you need to know two bits of information. <b style="color: rgb(254, 255, 93);">1) its name, prefixed with fa- (meaning ‚Äúfont awesome‚Äù naturally!)</b> and <b style="color: rgb(254, 255, 93);"> 2) the style you want to use‚Äôs corresponding prefix</b>.</p>
				
				<pre>
					<code class="bash">
					    <code class="css">
                                                                        <span style="color: chartreuse;">html</span>
  &lt;i class=<span class="bash-keyword">"fas fa-arrow-down"</span>&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;i class=<span class="bash-keyword">"fab fa-angellist"</span>&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;i class=<span class="bash-keyword">"fas fa-battery-half"</span>&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;i class=<span class="bash-keyword">"fas fa-basketball-ball"</span>&gt;&lt;/i&gt;

                        </code>
                    </code>
				</pre>

				<p> Will produce: </p>

				<p style="margin: 50px; text-align: center;">
					<i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i>
					<i class="fab fa-angellist"></i>
					<i class="fas fa-battery-half"></i>
					<i class="fas fa-basketball-ball"></i>
				</p>

				<p><b style="color: rgb(226, 31, 70);">Attention!</b> Before using it you need to sign in and <a href="https://fontawesome.com/start">get special key</a> at the original page. And this <b>key</b> has to be linked to your project as a stylesheet (read more: <a href="https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/on-the-web/referencing-icons/basic-use#additional-styling-options">Additional Styling Options</a>)</p>

